Columns.Name: EfxId
Columns.Description: The EFX ID™ is a unique and persistent nine-digit number that identifies and tracks the business unit with which you have the credit relationship;

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description:
Provides the timestamp when the inquiry was made as recorded
by Equifax (Eastern Time).

Columns.Name: ActivitySinceDate
Columns.Description: The date of inquiry.

Columns.Name: NumberOfAccountsUpdated
Columns.Description: The number of accounts updated.

Columns.Name: NumberOfNewAccountsOpened
Columns.Description: Number of accounts reported as open and active.

Columns.Name: NumberOfAccountsClosed
Columns.Description: Number of accounts which have been closed.

Columns.Name: RecentNumberOfAccountClosures
Columns.Description: The number of recent accounts closed.

Columns.Name: NumberOfNewDelinquenciesNonChargedOff
Columns.Description: Number of accounts which were previously "current" but have become delinquent (not charged-off) one or more times during the most recent 90 days.

Columns.Name: NumberOfNewChargeOffAccounts
Columns.Description: Number of accounts with an overall status of charged-off.

Columns.Name: ChargedOffAmount
Columns.Description:
Sum of the charged-off amount for the accounts reported as charged-off at the inquiry date. 

This value may be understated because one or more charged-off accounts didn't provide a dollar amount. It is possible that only a portion of the amount past due was charged-off; or could indicate a dispute.

Columns.Name: NumberOfInquiries
Columns.Description: Number of online inquiries made about this business.

Columns.Name: MostSevereStatusComment
Columns.Description:
Of the most recently reported opened and closed trades, the most severe status is returned.

Looks at the most recently reported credit experience of all reported open and closed accounts and returns the most severe status. Provides a view of how
that business is paying today.

Ex:
- Charge-off

Columns.Name: SingleHighestCreditExtendedAmount
Columns.Description: The single largest high credit, current credit, original credit or balance on an open account; closed accounts use balance only.

Columns.Name: TotalCurrentCreditExposureAmount
Columns.Description: Sums total outstanding balance on open and closed accounts.

Columns.Name: SingleHighestCreditExposureAmount
Columns.Description: The single largest high balance.

Columns.Name: TotalBalanceAmount
Columns.Description: Total reported balance, including owed but not yet due, and all past due amounts.

Columns.Name: MedianBalanceAmount
Columns.Description: The median balance of open, non charged-off accounts.

Columns.Name: AverageBalanceAmount
Columns.Description: Returns the average balance of open, non charged-off accounts.

Columns.Name: CurrentPortionOfBalanceDueAmount
Columns.Description: Total reported amount that has been charged but is not yet due or late.

Columns.Name: DelinquentNonChargedOffNumberOfAccounts
Columns.Description: Number of accounts which have an overall status of delinquent and not charged-off

Columns.Name: TotalPastDueAmount
Columns.Description: Total delinquent dollars (not charged-off).

Columns.Name: AtRiskBalanceAmount
Columns.Description: The total at risk balance amount.
